# Project skills (read when relevant)

This repo vendors skills under **`.agents/skills/<skill-name>/SKILL.md`**. For tasks that match a skill, **read that `SKILL.md` first** (use the Read tool) and follow its guidance alongside existing user rules.

| Task area | Skill folder | When |
|-----------|----------------|------|
| NestJS modules, DI, guards, microservices | `nestjs-best-practices` | `apps/*` Nest services, api-gateway |
| GraphQL schema / Apollo patterns | `graphql-schema` | api-gateway GraphQL, schema design |
| Mongoose / MongoDB | `mongoose-mongodb` | shop-svc, Mongo schemas |
| Postgres queries / perf / SQL | `supabase-postgres-best-practices` | user-svc, order-svc, TypeORM SQL |
| Express/Fastify-style Node APIs (general) | `nodejs-backend-patterns` | Cross-cutting backend patterns |
| React / client perf | `vercel-react-best-practices` | `apps/web` when tracked |

If multiple skills apply (e.g. Nest + GraphQL), read each relevant `SKILL.md` before large edits.

Keep skill usage proportional: small typo fixes do not require loading full skills; new features, refactors, or reviews should.
